# wind-chess-aesthetics.px — Visual & Audio Presentation Layer
#
# The game logic doesn't care about pixels or waveforms.
# This file does. It takes game events and produces:
#   - Visual effects (particles, screen shake, piece glow, board breathing)
#   - Sound cues (ambient wind, piece clicks, capture impacts, turbulence rumble)
#   - Juice (the 5% of effort that creates 80% of feel)
#
# Design principles:
#   - Every action has audio+visual feedback within 1 frame
#   - Intensity scales with game tension (quiet opening → chaotic endgame)
#   - Wind is VISIBLE and AUDIBLE at all times (the wind IS the game)
#   - Captures are celebrations, not just state changes
#   - Board is alive even when nobody is moving
#
# Queue topology:
#
#   frame_output ─→ [generate_vfx] ─→ visual_effects
#                                          │
#   game_events ─→ [generate_sfx] ─→ sound_cues
#                                          │
#   wind_field  ─→ [wind_ambience] ────────┤
#                                          ▼
#                                   [compose_presentation] ─→ presentation_frame
#

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Visual Effect Types
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

